===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|gml|da}} {{term|malen|mālen|to draw, paint|lang=gml}}. Cognate with Icelandic {{term|mála||to paint|lang=is}}.

====Verb====
{{head|da|verb|imperative|mal|present|maler|past|malede|or|malte|past participle|malet|or|malt}}

# to [[paint]]

=====Derived terms=====
* [[maler]] ("[[painter]]")
* [[maleri]] ("[[painting]]")
* [[maling]] ("[[paint]]")

===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|non|da}} {{term|mala|lang=non}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|da}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*malaną||to grind}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|da}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*melh₁-||to grind, rub, break up}}. Cognate with Icelandic {{term|mala|lang=is}}.

====Verb====
{{da-verb|mal|male|maler|malede|er/har|malet}}

